                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                                <desc>Beautiful hand. According to the catalogue, the scribe seems
                                    to be the same as the one of <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ANLcr9">Rome, Biblioteca dell’Accademia Nazionale dei Lincei, Conti Rossini 9</ref>.
                                    As the catalogue describes two different hands for <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ANLcr9">Rome, Biblioteca dell’Accademia Nazionale dei Lincei, Conti Rossini 9</ref>, this information is not entirely clear.</desc>
                                <seg type="ink">Black.</seg>
                            </handNote>                  
                        </handDesc>
          
          <decoDesc>
              <decoNote xml:id="d1" type="miniature">
                  <desc>On the first recto of the bifolio wrapped around the textblock, a polychrome miniature of a <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">More than 1 AT1035HolyMan</span></ref>
                      of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4322GabraMa">Gabra Maśiḥ</persName>, similar to the miniatures of  <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ANLcr9">Rome, Biblioteca dell’Accademia Nazionale dei Lincei, Conti Rossini 9</ref>, presumably copied from the
                      exemplar,  <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/GG00041">ኢሮብ፡, Gunda Gunde, C3-IV-7</ref> (though the catalogue does not state it).</desc>
                  <q xml:lang="gez">ስዕለ፡ ቅዱስ፡ አቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ መሲሕ፡ ሰላማዊ፡ ጸሎቱ፡ ትዕቀበነ፡
                      አሜን።</q>
              </decoNote>
          </decoDesc>
              
              <bindingDesc>
                  <binding contemporary="non-Ethiopian">
                      <decoNote xml:id="b1">European half-cloth binding. An unfoliated bifolio is wrapped around the textblock.</decoNote>
                  </binding>
              </bindingDesc>
          </physDesc>
                        
                        <history>
                            <origin><origDate notBefore="1900" notAfter="1949" evidence="lettering"/></origin>
                            <provenance>
                               The text of this manuscript was copied from <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/GG00041">ኢሮብ፡, Gunda Gunde, C3-IV-7</ref> from <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0005Gund">Gunda
                                        Gunde</placeName>. Two other <foreign xml:lang="gez">gadlāt</foreign> contained in <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/GG00041">ኢሮብ፡, Gunda Gunde, C3-IV-7</ref> were copied in <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ANLcr9">Rome, Biblioteca dell’Accademia Nazionale dei Lincei, Conti Rossini 9</ref>, possibly by the same
                                scribe. One codicological
                                unit of <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ANLcr9">Rome, Biblioteca dell’Accademia Nazionale dei Lincei, Conti Rossini 9</ref> was received by <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3182ContiRo">Carlo Conti Rossini</persName>
                                in 1925. A similar date of origin seems possible for this manuscript.
                            </provenance>
                            <acquisition>The manuscript passed into the possession of the library in <date when="1950">1950</date>, following Conti Rossini’s death in <date when="1949">1949</date> 
                                (see <ref target="https://www.menestrel.fr/?-Roma-&amp;lang=fr#845">Menestrel</ref>).</acquisition>
                        </history>
                        
